lab0.c:
     A C program implementation that allows the follwing options
     --input=[file name];
        user specification of the input file as stdin
     --output=file name]
        user specification of the output file as stdout
     --segfault
        Cause a segmentation fault by forcing an invlaid access to a null pointer
     --catch 
        Triggereed the handler and catch a SIGSEGV signal if the "--segfault" option is applied

Makefile 
    - lab0
        builds an executable lab0 from lab0.c with 
	    gcc -Wall -Wextra -g -o lab0 lab0.c
    - check
        run a shell script basictest.sh
        Test Includes:
            1) Check if the program can open an exsisiting file with input --option with no error
            2) Check if compare if the output print in stdout match with orginal file
            3) Test both --input and --output option when use together, by comparing if the specfic input and output file are identical 
            4) Check if error message is prompted and correct when an invalid input file is used with --input option 
            5) Check if error message is prompted and correct when an when unable to create a file with --output option 
            6) Test both 4 and 5 together when both --input and --output option are presented 
            7) Check if segmentation fault error is triggered when option --segfault is applied by check if exit status code is 139
            8) Check if the sigsegfault_handler propely catptures the segfault signal and prompt the correct error message when --segfault is applied
    - clean 
        remove all files and object created when using make command 
    - dist 
        Creaing a distribution tarball that including 
        lab0.c basictest.sh Makefile backtrace.png breakpoint.png README

        backtrace.png: 
        screenshot of the stack backtrace while running --segfault using gdb 

        breakpoint.png: 
        screenshot that inspect the pointer that trigger segfault while running --segfault 
        at the specfic breakpoint found in backtrace and prints the value of the pointer
	
	basictest.sh: a series of smoke test used by make check 




